<div class='row'>
  <div class='col-md-12'>
    <br />
    <h2>New Deployment: Select Cloud Infrastructure Products</h2>

    Choose the products to deploy. This wizard guides you through creating a new {{nameRedHat}} Cloud Infrastructure deployment.
    <br />
    <br />
  </div>
</div>

<div class='row' style='height:370px;'>

  <div class='col-md-4'>
    {{rchi-item srcImage=imgRhev isChecked=isRhev name=nameRhev cssId='is_rhev'}}
  </div>

  <div class='col-md-4'>
    {{rchi-item srcImage=imgOpenStack isChecked=isOpenStack name=nameOpenStack cssId='is_openstack'}}
  </div>

  <div class='col-md-4'>
    {{rchi-item srcImage=imgCloudForms isChecked=isCloudForms name=nameCloudForms cssId='is_cloudforms'}}
  </div>

</div>

{{#unless isUpstream}}
<div class='subscriptions_needed'>

  <i class="fa fa-info-circle"></i>
  <strong>Before you begin:</strong>

  <p>
    <strong>Subscriptions required to complete this deployment.</strong> Check your account in the <a href='https://idp.redhat.com/idp/' target='_blank'>Red Hat Customer Portal</a> to verify you have subscriptions available to cover the selected products.
    <br />
    <strong>Start up host machines.</strong> Ensure that the bare-metal computers and the virtual machines that you plan to use are turned on and discoverable.
    <br />
    <strong>Configure your network.</strong> Ensure that the network and subnets are set up and available.
  </p>

</div>
{{/unless}}

<br />
<div class='row'>
  <div class='col-md-12'>
    <div style='float:right;'>
      {{#link-to 'deployments' class="btn btn-default"}}Cancel{{/link-to}}
      {{#link-to satelliteTabRouteName class="btn btn-primary" disabled=disableNextOnStart}}Select{{/link-to}}
      {{!satelliteTabRouteName}}
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
